<br />
I tend to deck people rather fast and trust me do they hate it!  The WAY I deck people seems to annoy them the most.  My friend once shouted &quot;FAR-SEEING EYES ISNT SUPPOSE TO WORK LIKE THIS!&quot;  When I put down 4 elves in one turn.<br />
<br />
<br />
Then I foul feeted him (he played isengard orcs) and killed the rest of his hand.  Oh, good times.<br />
<br />
<br />
The deck is only weak (prone to pre site 6-loss) against non-twilight nazgul (i just slipped in the defiences and mirkwood) and really good swarm decks (i think, though I haven&#39;t tested that yet).  So playing those decks tend to ruin your fun.<br />
<br />
<br />
Oh well, that&#39;s it.<br />
<br />
<br />
By the way, u can normally make them discard 2 or more cards per turn (more as the game progresses).  Hell, I made my friend discard the top 6 cards off his deck and 4 cards from his hand (2 random) in one turn!  Prepare to laugh as u see Aragorn revealed from that silvery case flop into the discard pile right from the deck. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
